$ %SystemRoot\SysWOW64\SQLServerManager_n.msc

The *→ development/databases/SQL-Server configuration manager*.

The SQL Server configuration manager allows to adminster and configure
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/services[SQL Server services]
  • network connectivity (Client and server protocols)
  • Client aliases

The *SQL Server configuration manager* is a Windows tool. On → Linux, *mssql-conf* should be used instead.

{ Show installed instances and servies

  The SQL Server Configuration Manager can be used to determine which → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance[instances] are installed on a computer:
  gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/tools/Configuration-Manager/img/configuration-manager.png||

}

